# 
_pdbx_database_remark.id     700 
_pdbx_database_remark.text   
;SHEET 
THE *ACTIVE-SITE* SHEET SUBSTRUCTURE OF THIS MOLECULE HAS 
ONE EDGE-STRAND COMPRISED OF TWO DISTINCT SEQUENCES OF THE 
POLYPEPTIDE CHAIN.  TO REPRESENT THIS FEATURE AN EXTRA 
SHEET IS DEFINED.  STRANDS 2,3,4,5 OF S1 ARE IDENTICAL TO 
STRANDS 2,3,4,5 OF S2.
;
# 
_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                 4TMN 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details         
;THE ACTIVE SITE CLEFT OF THERMOLYSIN CONTAINS AT LEAST FOUR SUBSITES S1, S1(PRIME), S2, AND S2(PRIME) WHICH PARTICIPATE 
IN THE BINDING OF EXTENDED SUBSTRATES.  THEY ARE SPECIFIED ON *SITE* RECORDS BELOW.
;
